issue.title: Organized files into directories for refactoring, and more!
issue.body:
- Made `Logic/`and `Graphics/` directories to separate implementation from interface.
- Directories for refactored code: Objects, Properties, and Theorems are in the `Logic/` directory, and old code is placed in the `Logic/_old/` directory.
- Standardized the way theorems communicate their inputs through the `requires` field.
- New `ProofState` and `ObjectDB` objects handle the properties and objects of each proof. Makes for easy saving and coding.

issue.title: Redesign interface

milestone.title: Add interactive canvas graphics.
milestone.description: Objects drawn to canvas: selectable, draggable, and capable of interfacing cleanly with the back-end proof logic.

issue.body:
##### Goals:
- Easier to access elements through JS
- Add (hideable) sidebar with extra options as to saving/loading/changing modes
- Move theorem listing down to the same level as the proof bench, giving more space for the canvas graphics, and providing a more intuitive idea of where theorems should go
  - Hovering over theorems in the list brings up a tooltip with more information about it (clicking does as well)
  - Users can add lemmas through a `+`-sign button in the theorem listing pane
- More attractive colors
  - Given theorems and proven theorems have different coloring
##### Stretch:
- Be able to drag-drop theorems from listing to bench
- Hovering over the steps in the proof bench highlights the objects related to the step in the diagram pane
- User-modifiable interface (draggable boundaries, color schemes, etc.)
- Different workspaces for different subjects of proof-based mathematics
##### GUI Suggestions:

![pb_gui](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/1495572/14778982/c7a44090-0a8a-11e6-95c3-7419c75eb40c.png)
![pb_overlay](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/1495572/14778983/c7a7db2e-0a8a-11e6-869b-1610d72f3a3f.png)
